A woman who paid legal fees for convicted killer Joran van der 
Sloot, calling herself his 'guardian 
angel', has resigned from the case.

Mary Hamer, from Lake City, Florida, wrote a bizarre resignation letter saying she accepted defeat in the case, which found him guilty of murder.

Van der Sloot admitted to strangling Stephany Flores in May 2010 after she found out about his suspected involvement in the disappearance of U.S. teenager Natalee Holloway in 2005.

