The 24-year-old killer was sentenced to 28 years behind bars earlier this month.

Throughout the Peruvian case, divorced radiologist Hamer had protested his innocence and shelled out around $100,000 to cover his legal fees.

The letter, obtained by Radar Online, is addressed to President Obama, Peruvian president Ollanta Humala, the Flores family and Natalee Holloway's mother Beth.

It says Hamer 'accepts defeat' in the case, adding: 'The U.S. government & Peru have won the battle.'

